    <sTitle>Thermodynamics of the Pt-Cl system</sTitle>
    <sAbstract>We have proved existence three individual compounds in system of Pt Cl: PtCl4, PtCl3,  PtCl2, using static method (quartz membrane gauge zero pressure manometer). The  results of other authors about presence in the system of region existence PtCl were  refuted. The dissociation pressure of platinum chlorides has equilibrated for a very long  time, therefore we could approach the equilibrium only from the side of lower  pressures. Thus the values calculated from the tensimetric data have needed the  supplementary verification.  For this we have chosen the calorimetric method. In order to determine the enthalpies of  formation of platinum chlorides, we measured the heats of reduction of these  compounds with gaseous hydrogen.  Based on analysis of the obtained tensimetric and calorimetric data we have proposed  the system of thermodynamic characteristics of platinum chlorides.</sAbstract>
